6.label: Description
6.value:
4 large and 2 full-page miniatures with full borders, small illuminated initials and line-fillers.

nineteenth century blind-stamped brown leather binding, with spine repaired and metal fittings added.

Text and illumination on both sides of leaves. Verso of last leaf blank. Leaves numbered in pencil by a previous owner, but two leaves missed, thus pencilled leaf numbering ends at 106 instead of 108.

15.label: Notes
15.value:
Manuscript book of hours for the use of Rouen (including Calendar, Hours of the Virgin, Office of the Dead, and other prayers); written and illuminated in Rouen, France, approximately 1430-1440.

Artist: in the style of the Master of Sir John Fastolf, active in Rouen from approximately 1420 to 1449.

Title supplied by cataloguer.
